qas.question: Setting national renewable energy targets can be an important part of what?
The European Union has prescribed an indicative renewable energy target of what percent?

answers.text: 12 per cent of the total EU energy mix

qas.question: Name one outher country with defined national or regional target?

plausible_answers.text: 12 per cent of the total EU energy mix

qas.question: The European Union has not prescribed an indicative renewable energy target of what percent?
Name one other country without defined national or regional target?

context: Setting national renewable energy targets can be an important part of a <a0_0><b3_0><b4_0>renewable energy policy<b4_0/><b3_0/><a0_0/> and these targets are usually defined as a percentage of the primary energy and/or electricity generation mix. For example, the European Union has prescribed an indicative renewable energy target of <a1_0><b5_0>12 per cent of the total EU energy mix<b5_0/><a1_0/> and 22 per cent of electricity consumption by 2010. National targets for individual EU Member States have also been set to meet the overall target. Other developed countries with defined national or regional targets include <a2_0><b6_0>Australia<b6_0/><a2_0/>, Canada, Israel, Japan, Korea, New Zealand, Norway, Singapore, Switzerland, and some US States.
